item.title: What does this mean? how to fix it?
item.dc:creator: @me_caveman me caveman
item.description:
@me_caveman wrote:

[quote=“Scape-JAVA, post:2, topic:361101”]There is a case outside of a switch statement, therefore it is causing an orphaned case error something like this:

[code=java]
switch (example) {
case 1:
break;

    case 2:
    break;

}
case 3:
break;[/code]
That would be causing the error, the case is outside of a switch statement.[/quote]

yeah…sorry. i was retarded and didnt look at the faq. sometimes i forget simple things. thank you for the help.
